May you be liberated of all your sufferings.

67
00:08:39,292 --> 00:08:42,498
May you experience the peace and bliss of Nibbana.

68
00:08:47,787 --> 00:08:55,139
Continuing to raid it outwards till we've covered the whole of the earth, offering everyone worldly blessings.

69
00:09:19,623 --> 00:09:28,673
May you be free of greed and selfishness, hatred and ill will, fear and anxiety, ignorance and delusion.

70
00:09:30,616 --> 00:09:34,682
May you be kind and gentle, sympathetic and benevolent.

71
00:09:35,763 --> 00:09:38,066
May you be forgiving and compassionate.

72
00:09:39,347 --> 00:09:42,510
May you be joyful and rejoice in the success of others.

73
00:09:43,952 --> 00:09:45,755
May you be peaceful and calm.

74
00:09:46,897 --> 00:09:49,360
May you be liberated of all your sufferings.

75
00:09:50,234 --> 00:09:53,719
May you experience the peace and bliss of Nibbana.

76
00:09:59,688 --> 00:10:09,423
Pausing for a while to consider those areas where there's war, destitution, oppression.

77
00:10:25,097 --> 00:10:48,822
And now, choosing a phrase which most expresses whatever quality we wish to develop, be it love, compassion, joy or just peacefulness, a phrase such as, may all beings be happy, gently repeating it in our hearts and offering it to all beings, to all beings before us and behind us, to the left, to the right, below and above and all around.

78
00:10:51,384 --> 00:10:52,184
I shall chant

79
00:10:53,296 --> 00:10:55,138
The Discourse on Loving Kindness

80
00:11:01,868 --> 00:11:29,208
kāraṇīyaṁ gāta-kuṣalena yāntaṁ sāntaṁ padhaṁ gābhi-sāme ca sako uju ca suju ca suvā ca ca samudu anāti māni sāntu sako ca subhāro ca apā ki ca ca salāhu kāuti

81
00:11:29,543 --> 00:11:54,572
santindriyocchā nipakocchā apāgabokule suvānānugīdo nācā kūdāṃ samācāre kañcī ye na viṇyūpāre upāvā deyum sukhi no vākemi no hontu sābe sattā bhavantu sukhi tathā

82
00:11:55,514 --> 00:12:20,626
ye keci pāṇā-bhūtati tasā vātā-vāra-vāna-vasesa dhīgāvā ye mahānta-vāma-jīma-rasa-kaṇukātula dhītāvā ye vādhītā ye cādure vāsānti avidhūre

83
00:12:20,606 --> 00:12:45,788
bhūṭhā vāsaṁ pāveśi vāsābe sattā bhavantu sukhi tathā na paro parāṁ nīkubheta nāti maññata kathā cīnāṁ kañcī bhīyārosaṁ na pāttikāsāṁ yā naññā maññāsā dukkhaṁ gīcchēyā

84
00:12:46,206 --> 00:13:09,631
mātāyātāniyāṁ putaṁ gāyusāe kaputaṁ anurāge evaṁ pīsābhābhūteṣu mānasambhāvāye apārīmanāṁ me tencāsābhālokāsmiṁ mānasambhāvāye apārīmanāṁ

85
00:13:09,865 --> 00:13:34,049
Uddhāṁ ādo ca tīriyāṁ ca āsāṁ pātāṁ āverāṁ āsā pātāṁ Tītāṁ ca raṇṇi-sīno vāsā yāno vāyāvatā-savigātā-mīdho He táṁ satiṁ āditeyā brahmāṁ etāṁ vihāraṁ idamahū

86
00:13:35,076 --> 00:13:54,654
Dīṭiṁ ca nūpa-gaṁ āsīla-vāda-saṇena-saṁpāno Kāme suvi-ne āgedaṁ nāi jātu-gabhāseyaṁ puṇāre tīti

87
00:14:08,152 --> 00:14:18,006
Having established this goodwill, a heart of openness, generosity, compassion, let us now work with that area of forgivingness.

88
00:14:21,772 --> 00:14:33,669
First, bring to mind someone we have hurt, and as the incident comes to mind, the attendant emotions will arise, perhaps a feeling of self-righteousness,

89
00:14:35,253 --> 00:14:39,136
or a feeling of shame, guilt, remorse, whatever.

90
00:14:40,639 --> 00:14:44,523
As those emotions arise, we will have a reaction to them.

91
00:14:44,962 --> 00:14:54,952
We'll want to indulge our self-righteousness and we'll not want to feel or experience our sense of remorse or guilt.

92
00:14:57,855 --> 00:15:01,259
So, using that memory to contact these emotions

93
00:15:01,527 --> 00:15:12,644
and being wary not to allow the memory to shoot off into fantasy, but just to contact emotions, let those emotions arise, and let's see how we relate to them.

94
00:15:14,046 --> 00:15:22,860
Just working with that little vicious circle, the memory, the attendant emotions, and how we relate to those emotions.

95
00:15:44,812 --> 00:15:47,456
Can we see how we cause suffering for ourselves?

96
00:16:02,818 --> 00:16:12,253
Can we acknowledge these attitudes and emotions as unskillful, unwholesome, negative, life destructive, not life enhancing?

97
00:16:13,650 --> 00:16:21,441
undermining our capacity to love, to relate, leading only to more suffering, not the end of it.

98
00:16:38,864 --> 00:16:42,307
And the antidote, of course, is to ask for forgiveness.

99
00:16:42,811 --> 00:16:53,169
a rising out of, a sense of remorse, a desire to be reconciled, a desire to put right what we did wrong, a desire to compensate.

100
00:16:56,414 --> 00:17:04,650
Bringing that person to mind, let's talk about the situation with them and ask them to forgive us.

101
00:17:20,137 --> 00:17:33,375
Whatever harm I have done to you, in thought, word and deed, by way of greed, hatred and delusion, intentionally or unintentionally, please forgive me.

102
00:17:39,942 --> 00:17:46,652
Perhaps you can see a change in them, a desire in them to forgive, to become reconciled.

103
00:17:48,538 --> 00:17:50,422
Can you accept their hand of friendship?

104
00:17:51,923 --> 00:17:53,446
Can you accept their forgiveness?

105
00:17:54,828 --> 00:17:56,111
Can we forgive ourselves?

106
00:18:04,824 --> 00:18:07,087
Let's offer them some worldly blessings.

107
00:18:25,106 --> 00:18:34,000
May you be free of greed and selfishness hatred and ill will fear and anxiety ignorance and delusion.

108
00:18:35,342 --> 00:18:39,508
May you be kind and gentle sympathetic and benevolent.

109
00:18:41,250 --> 00:18:43,492
May you be forgiving and compassionate.

110
00:18:44,375 --> 00:18:47,880
May you be joyful and rejoice in the success of others.

111
00:18:49,582 --> 00:18:51,325
May you be peaceful and calm.

112
00:18:52,666 --> 00:18:55,029
May you be liberated of all your sufferings

113
00:18:56,291 --> 00:18:59,517
May you experience the peace and bliss of Nibbana.

114
00:19:07,488 --> 00:19:20,207
So, allowing that image to fade away, sensing that goodwill in our hearts, and let's bring to mind someone who has hurt us.

115
00:19:21,976 --> 00:19:31,498
And again, using that memory to contact feelings, emotions, the feelings of hurt, the feelings of revenge.

116
00:19:32,840 --> 00:19:39,916
And again, to see that reaction, how we don't want to feel the hurt, how we want to indulge our sense of revenge.

117
00:19:41,196 --> 00:19:53,068
just working with that little vicious circle, the memory, the attendant emotions, and our reaction to those emotions, being careful not to spin off into fantasy.

118
00:20:07,683 --> 00:20:10,426
Can we see how we cause suffering for ourselves,

119
00:20:27,248 --> 00:20:45,730
Can we acknowledge these attitudes and emotions as unskillful, unwholesome, negative, life-destructive, not life-enhancing, undermining our capacity to love, to relate, leading only to more suffering, not the end of it?

120
00:21:01,825 --> 00:21:03,867
And the antidote, of course, is to forgive.

121
00:21:03,907 --> 00:21:10,817
Remembering that to forgive is not to forget, it's not to excuse, it's not to condone.

122
00:21:10,857 --> 00:21:19,190
It's simply a change of attitude, away from revenge and hurt, towards understanding and compassion.

123
00:21:20,612 --> 00:21:23,496
Driven always by a desire to be reconciled.

124
00:21:26,227 --> 00:21:32,595
Let us bring that person to mind, talk about the event and offer them our forgiveness.

125
00:21:50,396 --> 00:21:52,740
Whatever harm you have done to me,

126
00:21:53,799 --> 00:22:04,752
in thought, word and deed, by way of greed, hatred and delusion, intentionally or unintentionally, I forgive you.

127
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:17,428
Perhaps we can see a change in them, a feeling of relief, a desire to be reconciled.

128
00:22:19,281 --> 00:22:24,047
Can we offer them a hand of friendship and with it worldly blessings?

129
00:22:35,357 --> 00:22:44,267
May you be free of greed and selfishness, hatred and ill-will, fear and anxiety, ignorance and delusion.

130
00:22:46,028 --> 00:22:47,871
May you be kind and gentle,

131
00:22:48,509 --> 00:22:51,973
sympathetic and benevolent.

132
00:22:51,993 --> 00:22:54,416
May you be forgiving and compassionate.

133
00:22:55,759 --> 00:22:59,103
May you be joyful and rejoice in the success of others.

134
00:23:01,066 --> 00:23:02,867
May you be peaceful and calm.

135
00:23:04,349 --> 00:23:06,653
May you be liberated of all your sufferings.

136
00:23:08,295 --> 00:23:11,799
May you experience the peace and bliss of Nibbāna.

137
00:23:19,069 --> 00:23:21,071
allowing that image to fade away.

138
00:23:21,092 --> 00:23:33,605
And now we've completed two of the four great efforts to develop what is beautiful in us and to get rid of what is ugly within us.

139
00:23:35,528 --> 00:23:42,194
The next two are to prevent further ugliness and to develop virtues which are not developed.

140
00:23:43,896 --> 00:23:44,637
So first,

141
00:23:45,901 --> 00:23:54,251
Let us recognize a certain trait, unskillful, unwholesome within us, which we don't want to develop.

142
00:23:57,115 --> 00:24:14,440
Using the four affirmations, I can, I am able to resist its temptation, I ought to for my own benefit and the benefit of others, I want to and I will,

143
00:24:16,596 --> 00:24:20,122
Can, ought, want, will.

144
00:24:36,002 --> 00:24:43,313
And let us make a resolution that should ever a temptation arise, we will be resolute not to fall to it.

145
00:24:46,903 --> 00:24:59,577
Sometimes there's a trait within us, a virtue which is not fully developed.

146
00:25:00,038 --> 00:25:04,041
Sometimes we see a virtue in another which we would like for ourselves.

147
00:25:04,782 --> 00:25:11,269
Again, using the four affirmations, I can, I am able to develop that virtue.

148
00:25:12,751 --> 00:25:15,914
I ought to, for my own benefit and the benefit of others.

149
00:25:16,907 --> 00:25:19,571
I want to, and I will.

150
00:25:37,798 --> 00:25:43,067
And let us make a resolve that should an occasion offer itself, we will practice that virtue.

151
00:25:52,513 --> 00:25:59,242
So again, let us turn that stream of compassion inwards and offer ourselves again some worldly blessings.

152
00:26:15,566 --> 00:26:18,190
May I be free of greed and selfishness.

153
00:26:19,411 --> 00:26:22,015
May I be free of hatred and ill will.

154
00:26:24,053 --> 00:26:51,057
May I be free of fear and anxiety May I be free of ignorance and delusion May I be kind and gentle, sympathetic and benevolent May I be forgiving and compassionate May I be joyful and rejoice in the success of others May I be peaceful and calm

155
00:26:52,623 --> 00:26:55,586
May I be liberated of all my sufferings.

156
00:26:57,628 --> 00:27:01,253
May I experience the peace and bliss of Nibbāna.

157
00:27:06,500 --> 00:27:14,230
And so finally, let us offer our goodwill once more to all beings in all directions.

158
00:27:16,594 --> 00:27:19,136
May all beings be free of physical pain

159
00:27:20,872 --> 00:27:23,655
May all beings be free of mental distress.

160
00:27:26,459 --> 00:27:29,844
May all beings be liberated of all their sufferings.

161
00:27:33,709 --> 00:27:36,251
May all beings live in contentment and joy.

162
00:27:38,454 --> 00:27:41,880
May all beings live together in peace and harmony.

163
00:27:44,383 --> 00:27:48,769
May all beings experience the peace and bliss of Nibbana.

164
00:27:52,292 --> 00:28:10,487
Sābe sāthā sukītā hantu Sābe sāthā sukītā hantu

165
00:28:14,263 --> 00:28:23,936
Sābe sātā sukītā hantū
